WEBVTT

00:00:00.360 --> 00:00:01.620
<v Instructor>So welcome to this section,</v>

00:00:01.620 --> 00:00:03.530
which is other AWS list services.

00:00:03.530 --> 00:00:06.980
So the idea in this section is that I'm going to give you

00:00:06.980 --> 00:00:09.420
an overview of other services that I couldn't group

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:11.790
with the other ones, and they're services

00:00:11.790 --> 00:00:13.790
that students did report to me as sometimes

00:00:13.790 --> 00:00:17.040
but rarely appearing on your AWS exam.

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:19.270
So I wanna keep this section short.

00:00:19.270 --> 00:00:20.620
So the lectures are going to be very short

00:00:20.620 --> 00:00:23.650
and brief and most likely without any hands-on, okay?

00:00:23.650 --> 00:00:25.400
And there's going to be no summary lecture

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:27.580
at the end of this section, so I can keep things flexible

00:00:27.580 --> 00:00:30.050
and keep on adding services to the section

00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:32.020
in case I hear feedback from students.

00:00:32.020 --> 00:00:33.450
It's going to be very easy.

00:00:33.450 --> 00:00:36.940
It's one service and one definition, so don't stress

00:00:36.940 --> 00:00:38.350
if you don't understand the service directly.

00:00:38.350 --> 00:00:39.450
Just remember the definition,

00:00:39.450 --> 00:00:41.360
